The paper deals with formal logic for quantitative reasoning about security properties of network protocols, which is a core topic in the field of cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves reasoning about protocol invariants and concrete security bounds, which are topics covered in sub-categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses digital signatures and pseudorandom number generators, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
